<name>DIAGNOSTIC TROUBLE CODE CHART</name>
<subpara id="RM000000W7101XX_z0" proc-id="RM0250U___000033D00000">
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>If a DTC is displayed during the DTC check, check the parts listed in the table below and proceed to the page given.</ptxt>
<atten4>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>*1: MIL (Malfunction Indicator Lamp) comes on</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>*2: "DTC stored" mark means TCM memorizes the trouble code if the TCM detects that the DTC detection condition is satisfied.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>A DTC may be output when the clutch, brake and gear components, etc. inside the automatic transaxle are damaged.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten4>
